{"type":"message","id":"f2164272","parentId":"7a3c1686","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:29:07.890Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uohywic4d2u5_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"MiniMax\n\n  /**\n   * Convert text to audio with a given voice and save the output audio file to a given directory. If no\n   * directory is provided, the file will be saved to desktop. If no voice ID is provided, the default\n   * voice will be used.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param text Text to convert to audio\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   * @param voiceId? Voice ID to use, e.g. \"female-shaonv\"\n   * @param model? Model to use\n   * @param speed? Speech speed\n   * @param vol? Speech volume\n   * @param pitch? Speech pitch\n   * @param emotion? Speech emotion, values: [\"happy\", \"sad\", \"angry\", \"fearful\", \"disgusted\",\n   *                 \"surprised\", \"neutral\"]\n   * @param format? Audio format, values: [\"pcm\", \"mp3\",\"flac\", \"wav\"]\n   * @param sampleRate? Sample rate (Hz), values: [8000, 16000, 22050, 24000, 32000, 44100]\n   * @param bitrate? Bitrate (bps), values: [64000, 96000, 128000, 160000, 192000, 224000, 256000,\n   *                 320000]\n   * @param channel? Audio channels, values: [1, 2]\n   * @param languageBoost? Enhance the ability to recognize specified languages and dialects. Supported\n   *                       values include: 'Chinese', 'Chinese,Yue', 'English', 'Arabic', 'Russian',\n   *                       'Spanish', 'French', 'Portuguese', 'German', 'Turkish', 'Dutch', 'Ukrainian',\n   *                       'Vietnamese', 'Indonesian', 'Japanese', 'Italian', 'Korean', 'Thai', 'Polish',\n   *                       'Romanian', 'Greek', 'Czech', 'Finnish', 'Hindi', 'auto', default is 'auto'\n   * @param subtitleEnable? The parameter controls whether the subtitle service is enabled. The model\n   *                        must be 'speech-01-turbo' or 'speech-01-hd'. If this parameter is not\n   *                        provided, the default value is false\n   * @param outputFile? Path to save the generated audio file, automatically generated if not provided\n   */\n  function text_to_audio(text: string, outputDirectory?: string, voiceId?: string, model?: string, speed?: number);\n  // optional (10): vol, pitch, emotion, format, sampleRate, ...\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"text\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Text to convert to audio\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          },\n          \"voiceId\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"male-qn-qingse\",\n            \"description\": \"Voice ID to use, e.g. \\\"female-shaonv\\\"\"\n          },\n          \"model\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"speech-02-hd\",\n            \"description\": \"Model to use\"\n          },\n          \"speed\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"minimum\": 0.5,\n            \"maximum\": 2,\n            \"default\": 1,\n            \"description\": \"Speech speed\"\n          },\n          \"vol\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"minimum\": 0.1,\n            \"maximum\": 10,\n            \"default\": 1,\n            \"description\": \"Speech volume\"\n          },\n          \"pitch\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"minimum\": -12,\n            \"maximum\": 12,\n            \"default\": 0,\n            \"description\": \"Speech pitch\"\n          },\n          \"emotion\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"happy\",\n            \"description\": \"Speech emotion, values: [\\\"happy\\\", \\\"sad\\\", \\\"angry\\\", \\\"fearful\\\", \\\"disgusted\\\", \\\"surprised\\\", \\\"neutral\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"format\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"mp3\",\n            \"description\": \"Audio format, values: [\\\"pcm\\\", \\\"mp3\\\",\\\"flac\\\", \\\"wav\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"sampleRate\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"default\": 32000,\n            \"description\": \"Sample rate (Hz), values: [8000, 16000, 22050, 24000, 32000, 44100]\"\n          },\n          \"bitrate\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"default\": 128000,\n            \"description\": \"Bitrate (bps), values: [64000, 96000, 128000, 160000, 192000, 224000, 256000, 320000]\"\n          },\n          \"channel\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"default\": 1,\n            \"description\": \"Audio channels, values: [1, 2]\"\n          },\n          \"languageBoost\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"auto\",\n            \"description\": \"Enhance the ability to recognize specified languages and dialects. Supported values include: 'Chinese', 'Chinese,Yue', 'English', 'Arabic', 'Russian', 'Spanish', 'French', 'Portuguese', 'German', 'Turkish', 'Dutch', 'Ukrainian', 'Vietnamese', 'Indonesian', 'Japanese', 'Italian', 'Korean', 'Thai', 'Polish', 'Romanian', 'Greek', 'Czech', 'Finnish', 'Hindi', 'auto', default is 'auto'\"\n          },\n          \"subtitleEnable\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false,\n            \"description\": \"The parameter controls whether the subtitle service is enabled. The model must be 'speech-01-turbo' or 'speech-01-hd'. If this parameter is not provided, the default value is false\"\n          },\n          \"outputFile\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to save the generated audio file, automatically generated if not provided\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"text\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * List all available voices. Only supported when api_host is https://api.minimax.chat.\n   *\n   * @param voiceType? Type of voices to list, values: [\"all\", \"system\", \"voice_cloning\"]\n   */\n  function list_voices(voiceType?: string);\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"voiceType\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"all\",\n            \"description\": \"Type of voices to list, values: [\\\"all\\\", \\\"system\\\", \\\"voice_cloning\\\"]\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Play an audio file. Supports WAV and MP3 formats. Does not support video.\n   *\n   * @param inputFilePath Path to the audio file to play\n   * @param isUrl? Whether the audio file is a URL\n   */\n  function play_audio(inputFilePath: string, isUrl?: boolean);\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"inputFilePath\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to the audio file to play\"\n          },\n          \"isUrl\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false,\n            \"description\": \"Whether the audio file is a URL\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"inputFilePath\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Clone a voice using the provided audio file. New voices will incur costs when first used.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param voiceId Voice ID to use\n   * @param audioFile Path to the audio file\n   * @param text? Text for the demo audio\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   * @param isUrl? Whether the audio file is a URL\n   */\n  function voice_clone(voiceId: string, audioFile: string, text?: string, outputDirectory?: string, isUrl?: boolean);\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"voiceId\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Voice ID to use\"\n          },\n          \"audioFile\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to the audio file\"\n          },\n          \"text\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Text for the demo audio\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          },\n          \"isUrl\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false,\n            \"description\": \"Whether the audio file is a URL\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"voiceId\",\n          \"audioFile\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Generate images based on text prompts.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param model? Model to use\n   * @param prompt Text prompt for image generation\n   * @param aspectRatio? Image aspect ratio, values: [\"1:1\", \"16:9\",\"4:3\", \"3:2\", \"2:3\", \"3:4\", \"9:16\",\n   *                     \"21:9\"]\n   * @param n? Number of images to generate\n   * @param promptOptimizer? Whether to optimize the prompt\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   * @param outputFile? Path to save the generated image file, automatically generated if not provided\n   */\n  function text_to_image(model?: string, prompt: string, aspectRatio?: string, n?: number, promptOptimizer?: boolean);\n  // optional (2): outputDirectory, outputFile\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"model\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"image-01\",\n            \"description\": \"Model to use\"\n          },\n          \"prompt\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Text prompt for image generation\"\n          },\n          \"aspectRatio\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"1:1\",\n            \"description\": \"Image aspect ratio, values: [\\\"1:1\\\", \\\"16:9\\\",\\\"4:3\\\", \\\"3:2\\\", \\\"2:3\\\", \\\"3:4\\\", \\\"9:16\\\", \\\"21:9\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"n\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"minimum\": 1,\n            \"maximum\": 9,\n            \"default\": 1,\n            \"description\": \"Number of images to generate\"\n          },\n          \"promptOptimizer\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": true,\n            \"description\": \"Whether to optimize the prompt\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          },\n          \"outputFile\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to save the generated image file, automatically generated if not provided\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"prompt\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Generate a video based on text prompts.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param model? Model to use, values: [\"T2V-01\", \"T2V-01-Director\", \"I2V-01\", \"I2V-01-Director\",\n   *               \"I2V-01-live\", \"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\"]\n   * @param prompt Text prompt for video generation\n   * @param firstFrameImage? First frame image\n   * @param duration? The duration of the video. The model must be \"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\". Values can be 6\n   *                  and 10.\n   * @param resolution? The resolution of the video. The model must be \"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\". Values range\n   *                    [\"768P\", \"1080P\"]\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   * @param outputFile? Path to save the generated video file, automatically generated if not provided\n   * @param asyncMode? Whether to use async mode. Defaults to False. If True, the video generation task\n   *                   will be submitted asynchronously and the response will return a task_id. Should\n   *                   use `query_video_generation` tool to check the status of the task and get the\n   *                   result.\n   */\n  function generate_video(model?: string, prompt: string, firstFrameImage?: string, duration?: number, resolution?: string);\n  // optional (3): outputDirectory, outputFile, asyncMode\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"model\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\",\n            \"description\": \"Model to use, values: [\\\"T2V-01\\\", \\\"T2V-01-Director\\\", \\\"I2V-01\\\", \\\"I2V-01-Director\\\", \\\"I2V-01-live\\\", \\\"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"prompt\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Text prompt for video generation\"\n          },\n          \"firstFrameImage\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"First frame image\"\n          },\n          \"duration\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"description\": \"The duration of the video. The model must be \\\"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\\\". Values can be 6 and 10.\"\n          },\n          \"resolution\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The resolution of the video. The model must be \\\"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\\\". Values range [\\\"768P\\\", \\\"1080P\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          },\n          \"outputFile\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to save the generated video file, automatically generated if not provided\"\n          },\n          \"asyncMode\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false,\n            \"description\": \"Whether to use async mode. Defaults to False. If True, the video generation task will be submitted asynchronously and the response will return a task_id. Should use `query_video_generation` tool to check the status of the task and get the result.\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"prompt\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Generate a video based on an image.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param model? Model to use, values: [\"I2V-01\", \"I2V-01-Director\", \"I2V-01-live\"]\n   * @param prompt Text prompt for video generation\n   * @param firstFrameImage Path to the first frame image\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   * @param outputFile? Path to save the generated video file, automatically generated if not provided\n   * @param asyncMode? Whether to use async mode. Defaults to False. If True, the video generation task\n   *                   will be submitted asynchronously and the response will return a task_id. Should\n   *                   use `query_video_generation` tool to check the status of the task and get the\n   *                   result.\n   */\n  function image_to_video(model?: string, prompt: string, firstFrameImage: string, outputDirectory?: string, outputFile?: string);\n  // optional (1): asyncMode\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"model\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"I2V-01\",\n            \"description\": \"Model to use, values: [\\\"I2V-01\\\", \\\"I2V-01-Director\\\", \\\"I2V-01-live\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"prompt\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Text prompt for video generation\"\n          },\n          \"firstFrameImage\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to the first frame image\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          },\n          \"outputFile\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to save the generated video file, automatically generated if not provided\"\n          },\n          \"asyncMode\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false,\n            \"description\": \"Whether to use async mode. Defaults to False. If True, the video generation task will be submitted asynchronously and the response will return a task_id. Should use `query_video_generation` tool to check the status of the task and get the result.\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"prompt\",\n          \"firstFrameImage\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Query the status of a video generation task.\n   *\n   * @param taskId The Task ID to query. Should be the task_id returned by `generate_video` tool if\n   *               `async_mode` is True.\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   */\n  function query_video_generation(taskId: string, outputDirectory?: string);\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"taskId\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The Task ID to query. Should be the task_id returned by `generate_video` tool if `async_mode` is True.\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"taskId\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Create a music generation task using AI models. Generate music from prompt and lyrics.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param prompt Music creation inspiration describing style, mood, scene, etc.\n   *               Example: \"Pop music, sad, suitable for rainy nights\". Character range: [10, 300]\n   * @param lyrics Song lyrics for music generation.\n   *               Use newline (\\n) to separate each line of lyrics. Supports lyric structure tags\n   *               [Intro][Verse][Chorus][Bridge][Outro]\n   *               to enhance musicality. Character range: [10, 600] (each Chinese character,\n   *               punctuation, and letter counts as 1 character)\n   * @param sampleRate? Sample rate of generated music. Values: [16000, 24000, 32000, 44100]\n   * @param bitrate? Bitrate of generated music. Values: [32000, 64000, 128000, 256000]\n   * @param format? Format of generated music. Values: [\"mp3\", \"wav\", \"pcm\"]\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   */\n  function music_generation(prompt: string, lyrics: string, sampleRate?: number, bitrate?: number, format?: string);\n  // optional (1): outputDirectory\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"prompt\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Music creation inspiration describing style, mood, scene, etc.\\nExample: \\\"Pop music, sad, suitable for rainy nights\\\". Character range: [10, 300]\"\n          },\n          \"lyrics\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Song lyrics for music generation.\\nUse newline (\\\\n) to separate each line of lyrics. Supports lyric structure tags [Intro][Verse][Chorus][Bridge][Outro]\\nto enhance musicality. Character range: [10, 600] (each Chinese character, punctuation, and letter counts as 1 character)\"\n          },\n          \"sampleRate\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"default\": 32000,\n            \"description\": \"Sample rate of generated music. Values: [16000, 24000, 32000, 44100]\"\n          },\n          \"bitrate\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"default\": 128000,\n            \"description\": \"Bitrate of generated music. Values: [32000, 64000, 128000, 256000]\"\n          },\n          \"format\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"mp3\",\n            \"description\": \"Format of generated music. Values: [\\\"mp3\\\", \\\"wav\\\", \\\"pcm\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"prompt\",\n          \"lyrics\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Generate a voice based on description prompts.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param prompt The prompt to generate the voice from\n   * @param previewText The text to preview the voice\n   * @param voiceId? The id of the voice to use. For example,\n   *                 \"male-qn-qingse\"/\"audiobook_female_1\"/\"cute_boy\"/\"Charming_Lady\"...\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   */\n  function voice_design(prompt: string, previewText: string, voiceId?: string, outputDirectory?: string);\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"prompt\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The prompt to generate the voice from\"\n          },\n          \"previewText\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The text to preview the voice\"\n          },\n          \"voiceId\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The id of the voice to use. For example, \\\"male-qn-qingse\\\"/\\\"audiobook_female_1\\\"/\\\"cute_boy\\\"/\\\"Charming_Lady\\\"...\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"prompt\",\n          \"previewText\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  Examples:\n    mcporter call MiniMax.text_to_audio(text: \"value\", voiceId: \"male-qn-qings, ...)\n\n  Optional parameters hidden; run with --all-parameters to view all fields.\n\n  10 tools · 496ms · STDIO minimax-mcp-js"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":876,"aggregated":"MiniMax\n\n  /**\n   * Convert text to audio with a given voice and save the output audio file to a given directory. If no\n   * directory is provided, the file will be saved to desktop. If no voice ID is provided, the default\n   * voice will be used.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param text Text to convert to audio\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   * @param voiceId? Voice ID to use, e.g. \"female-shaonv\"\n   * @param model? Model to use\n   * @param speed? Speech speed\n   * @param vol? Speech volume\n   * @param pitch? Speech pitch\n   * @param emotion? Speech emotion, values: [\"happy\", \"sad\", \"angry\", \"fearful\", \"disgusted\",\n   *                 \"surprised\", \"neutral\"]\n   * @param format? Audio format, values: [\"pcm\", \"mp3\",\"flac\", \"wav\"]\n   * @param sampleRate? Sample rate (Hz), values: [8000, 16000, 22050, 24000, 32000, 44100]\n   * @param bitrate? Bitrate (bps), values: [64000, 96000, 128000, 160000, 192000, 224000, 256000,\n   *                 320000]\n   * @param channel? Audio channels, values: [1, 2]\n   * @param languageBoost? Enhance the ability to recognize specified languages and dialects. Supported\n   *                       values include: 'Chinese', 'Chinese,Yue', 'English', 'Arabic', 'Russian',\n   *                       'Spanish', 'French', 'Portuguese', 'German', 'Turkish', 'Dutch', 'Ukrainian',\n   *                       'Vietnamese', 'Indonesian', 'Japanese', 'Italian', 'Korean', 'Thai', 'Polish',\n   *                       'Romanian', 'Greek', 'Czech', 'Finnish', 'Hindi', 'auto', default is 'auto'\n   * @param subtitleEnable? The parameter controls whether the subtitle service is enabled. The model\n   *                        must be 'speech-01-turbo' or 'speech-01-hd'. If this parameter is not\n   *                        provided, the default value is false\n   * @param outputFile? Path to save the generated audio file, automatically generated if not provided\n   */\n  function text_to_audio(text: string, outputDirectory?: string, voiceId?: string, model?: string, speed?: number);\n  // optional (10): vol, pitch, emotion, format, sampleRate, ...\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"text\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Text to convert to audio\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          },\n          \"voiceId\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"male-qn-qingse\",\n            \"description\": \"Voice ID to use, e.g. \\\"female-shaonv\\\"\"\n          },\n          \"model\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"speech-02-hd\",\n            \"description\": \"Model to use\"\n          },\n          \"speed\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"minimum\": 0.5,\n            \"maximum\": 2,\n            \"default\": 1,\n            \"description\": \"Speech speed\"\n          },\n          \"vol\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"minimum\": 0.1,\n            \"maximum\": 10,\n            \"default\": 1,\n            \"description\": \"Speech volume\"\n          },\n          \"pitch\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"minimum\": -12,\n            \"maximum\": 12,\n            \"default\": 0,\n            \"description\": \"Speech pitch\"\n          },\n          \"emotion\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"happy\",\n            \"description\": \"Speech emotion, values: [\\\"happy\\\", \\\"sad\\\", \\\"angry\\\", \\\"fearful\\\", \\\"disgusted\\\", \\\"surprised\\\", \\\"neutral\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"format\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"mp3\",\n            \"description\": \"Audio format, values: [\\\"pcm\\\", \\\"mp3\\\",\\\"flac\\\", \\\"wav\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"sampleRate\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"default\": 32000,\n            \"description\": \"Sample rate (Hz), values: [8000, 16000, 22050, 24000, 32000, 44100]\"\n          },\n          \"bitrate\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"default\": 128000,\n            \"description\": \"Bitrate (bps), values: [64000, 96000, 128000, 160000, 192000, 224000, 256000, 320000]\"\n          },\n          \"channel\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"default\": 1,\n            \"description\": \"Audio channels, values: [1, 2]\"\n          },\n          \"languageBoost\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"auto\",\n            \"description\": \"Enhance the ability to recognize specified languages and dialects. Supported values include: 'Chinese', 'Chinese,Yue', 'English', 'Arabic', 'Russian', 'Spanish', 'French', 'Portuguese', 'German', 'Turkish', 'Dutch', 'Ukrainian', 'Vietnamese', 'Indonesian', 'Japanese', 'Italian', 'Korean', 'Thai', 'Polish', 'Romanian', 'Greek', 'Czech', 'Finnish', 'Hindi', 'auto', default is 'auto'\"\n          },\n          \"subtitleEnable\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false,\n            \"description\": \"The parameter controls whether the subtitle service is enabled. The model must be 'speech-01-turbo' or 'speech-01-hd'. If this parameter is not provided, the default value is false\"\n          },\n          \"outputFile\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to save the generated audio file, automatically generated if not provided\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"text\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * List all available voices. Only supported when api_host is https://api.minimax.chat.\n   *\n   * @param voiceType? Type of voices to list, values: [\"all\", \"system\", \"voice_cloning\"]\n   */\n  function list_voices(voiceType?: string);\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"voiceType\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"all\",\n            \"description\": \"Type of voices to list, values: [\\\"all\\\", \\\"system\\\", \\\"voice_cloning\\\"]\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Play an audio file. Supports WAV and MP3 formats. Does not support video.\n   *\n   * @param inputFilePath Path to the audio file to play\n   * @param isUrl? Whether the audio file is a URL\n   */\n  function play_audio(inputFilePath: string, isUrl?: boolean);\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"inputFilePath\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to the audio file to play\"\n          },\n          \"isUrl\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false,\n            \"description\": \"Whether the audio file is a URL\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"inputFilePath\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Clone a voice using the provided audio file. New voices will incur costs when first used.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param voiceId Voice ID to use\n   * @param audioFile Path to the audio file\n   * @param text? Text for the demo audio\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   * @param isUrl? Whether the audio file is a URL\n   */\n  function voice_clone(voiceId: string, audioFile: string, text?: string, outputDirectory?: string, isUrl?: boolean);\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"voiceId\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Voice ID to use\"\n          },\n          \"audioFile\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to the audio file\"\n          },\n          \"text\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Text for the demo audio\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          },\n          \"isUrl\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false,\n            \"description\": \"Whether the audio file is a URL\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"voiceId\",\n          \"audioFile\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Generate images based on text prompts.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param model? Model to use\n   * @param prompt Text prompt for image generation\n   * @param aspectRatio? Image aspect ratio, values: [\"1:1\", \"16:9\",\"4:3\", \"3:2\", \"2:3\", \"3:4\", \"9:16\",\n   *                     \"21:9\"]\n   * @param n? Number of images to generate\n   * @param promptOptimizer? Whether to optimize the prompt\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   * @param outputFile? Path to save the generated image file, automatically generated if not provided\n   */\n  function text_to_image(model?: string, prompt: string, aspectRatio?: string, n?: number, promptOptimizer?: boolean);\n  // optional (2): outputDirectory, outputFile\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"model\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"image-01\",\n            \"description\": \"Model to use\"\n          },\n          \"prompt\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Text prompt for image generation\"\n          },\n          \"aspectRatio\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"1:1\",\n            \"description\": \"Image aspect ratio, values: [\\\"1:1\\\", \\\"16:9\\\",\\\"4:3\\\", \\\"3:2\\\", \\\"2:3\\\", \\\"3:4\\\", \\\"9:16\\\", \\\"21:9\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"n\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"minimum\": 1,\n            \"maximum\": 9,\n            \"default\": 1,\n            \"description\": \"Number of images to generate\"\n          },\n          \"promptOptimizer\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": true,\n            \"description\": \"Whether to optimize the prompt\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          },\n          \"outputFile\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to save the generated image file, automatically generated if not provided\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"prompt\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Generate a video based on text prompts.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param model? Model to use, values: [\"T2V-01\", \"T2V-01-Director\", \"I2V-01\", \"I2V-01-Director\",\n   *               \"I2V-01-live\", \"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\"]\n   * @param prompt Text prompt for video generation\n   * @param firstFrameImage? First frame image\n   * @param duration? The duration of the video. The model must be \"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\". Values can be 6\n   *                  and 10.\n   * @param resolution? The resolution of the video. The model must be \"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\". Values range\n   *                    [\"768P\", \"1080P\"]\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   * @param outputFile? Path to save the generated video file, automatically generated if not provided\n   * @param asyncMode? Whether to use async mode. Defaults to False. If True, the video generation task\n   *                   will be submitted asynchronously and the response will return a task_id. Should\n   *                   use `query_video_generation` tool to check the status of the task and get the\n   *                   result.\n   */\n  function generate_video(model?: string, prompt: string, firstFrameImage?: string, duration?: number, resolution?: string);\n  // optional (3): outputDirectory, outputFile, asyncMode\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"model\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\",\n            \"description\": \"Model to use, values: [\\\"T2V-01\\\", \\\"T2V-01-Director\\\", \\\"I2V-01\\\", \\\"I2V-01-Director\\\", \\\"I2V-01-live\\\", \\\"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"prompt\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Text prompt for video generation\"\n          },\n          \"firstFrameImage\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"First frame image\"\n          },\n          \"duration\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"description\": \"The duration of the video. The model must be \\\"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\\\". Values can be 6 and 10.\"\n          },\n          \"resolution\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The resolution of the video. The model must be \\\"MiniMax-Hailuo-02\\\". Values range [\\\"768P\\\", \\\"1080P\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          },\n          \"outputFile\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to save the generated video file, automatically generated if not provided\"\n          },\n          \"asyncMode\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false,\n            \"description\": \"Whether to use async mode. Defaults to False. If True, the video generation task will be submitted asynchronously and the response will return a task_id. Should use `query_video_generation` tool to check the status of the task and get the result.\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"prompt\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Generate a video based on an image.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param model? Model to use, values: [\"I2V-01\", \"I2V-01-Director\", \"I2V-01-live\"]\n   * @param prompt Text prompt for video generation\n   * @param firstFrameImage Path to the first frame image\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   * @param outputFile? Path to save the generated video file, automatically generated if not provided\n   * @param asyncMode? Whether to use async mode. Defaults to False. If True, the video generation task\n   *                   will be submitted asynchronously and the response will return a task_id. Should\n   *                   use `query_video_generation` tool to check the status of the task and get the\n   *                   result.\n   */\n  function image_to_video(model?: string, prompt: string, firstFrameImage: string, outputDirectory?: string, outputFile?: string);\n  // optional (1): asyncMode\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"model\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"I2V-01\",\n            \"description\": \"Model to use, values: [\\\"I2V-01\\\", \\\"I2V-01-Director\\\", \\\"I2V-01-live\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"prompt\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Text prompt for video generation\"\n          },\n          \"firstFrameImage\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to the first frame image\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          },\n          \"outputFile\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Path to save the generated video file, automatically generated if not provided\"\n          },\n          \"asyncMode\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false,\n            \"description\": \"Whether to use async mode. Defaults to False. If True, the video generation task will be submitted asynchronously and the response will return a task_id. Should use `query_video_generation` tool to check the status of the task and get the result.\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"prompt\",\n          \"firstFrameImage\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Query the status of a video generation task.\n   *\n   * @param taskId The Task ID to query. Should be the task_id returned by `generate_video` tool if\n   *               `async_mode` is True.\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   */\n  function query_video_generation(taskId: string, outputDirectory?: string);\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"taskId\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The Task ID to query. Should be the task_id returned by `generate_video` tool if `async_mode` is True.\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"taskId\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Create a music generation task using AI models. Generate music from prompt and lyrics.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param prompt Music creation inspiration describing style, mood, scene, etc.\n   *               Example: \"Pop music, sad, suitable for rainy nights\". Character range: [10, 300]\n   * @param lyrics Song lyrics for music generation.\n   *               Use newline (\\n) to separate each line of lyrics. Supports lyric structure tags\n   *               [Intro][Verse][Chorus][Bridge][Outro]\n   *               to enhance musicality. Character range: [10, 600] (each Chinese character,\n   *               punctuation, and letter counts as 1 character)\n   * @param sampleRate? Sample rate of generated music. Values: [16000, 24000, 32000, 44100]\n   * @param bitrate? Bitrate of generated music. Values: [32000, 64000, 128000, 256000]\n   * @param format? Format of generated music. Values: [\"mp3\", \"wav\", \"pcm\"]\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   */\n  function music_generation(prompt: string, lyrics: string, sampleRate?: number, bitrate?: number, format?: string);\n  // optional (1): outputDirectory\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"prompt\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Music creation inspiration describing style, mood, scene, etc.\\nExample: \\\"Pop music, sad, suitable for rainy nights\\\". Character range: [10, 300]\"\n          },\n          \"lyrics\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"Song lyrics for music generation.\\nUse newline (\\\\n) to separate each line of lyrics. Supports lyric structure tags [Intro][Verse][Chorus][Bridge][Outro]\\nto enhance musicality. Character range: [10, 600] (each Chinese character, punctuation, and letter counts as 1 character)\"\n          },\n          \"sampleRate\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"default\": 32000,\n            \"description\": \"Sample rate of generated music. Values: [16000, 24000, 32000, 44100]\"\n          },\n          \"bitrate\": {\n            \"type\": \"number\",\n            \"default\": 128000,\n            \"description\": \"Bitrate of generated music. Values: [32000, 64000, 128000, 256000]\"\n          },\n          \"format\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"default\": \"mp3\",\n            \"description\": \"Format of generated music. Values: [\\\"mp3\\\", \\\"wav\\\", \\\"pcm\\\"]\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"prompt\",\n          \"lyrics\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  /**\n   * Generate a voice based on description prompts.\n   * Note: This tool calls MiniMax API and may incur costs. Use only when explicitly requested by the\n   * user.\n   *\n   * @param prompt The prompt to generate the voice from\n   * @param previewText The text to preview the voice\n   * @param voiceId? The id of the voice to use. For example,\n   *                 \"male-qn-qingse\"/\"audiobook_female_1\"/\"cute_boy\"/\"Charming_Lady\"...\n   * @param outputDirectory? The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is\n   *                         `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if\n   *                         `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the\n   *                         output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\n   */\n  function voice_design(prompt: string, previewText: string, voiceId?: string, outputDirectory?: string);\n      {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"prompt\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The prompt to generate the voice from\"\n          },\n          \"previewText\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The text to preview the voice\"\n          },\n          \"voiceId\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The id of the voice to use. For example, \\\"male-qn-qingse\\\"/\\\"audiobook_female_1\\\"/\\\"cute_boy\\\"/\\\"Charming_Lady\\\"...\"\n          },\n          \"outputDirectory\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The directory to save the output file. `outputDirectory` is relative to `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH` (or `basePath` in config). The final save path is `${basePath}/${outputDirectory}`. For example, if `MINIMAX_MCP_BASE_PATH=~/Desktop` and `outputDirectory=workspace`, the output will be saved to `~/Desktop/workspace/`\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"prompt\",\n          \"previewText\"\n        ],\n        \"additionalProperties\": false,\n        \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"\n      }\n\n  Examples:\n    mcporter call MiniMax.text_to_audio(text: \"value\", voiceId: \"male-qn-qings, ...)\n\n  Optional parameters hidden; run with --all-parameters to view all fields.\n\n  10 tools · 496ms · STDIO minimax-mcp-js","cwd":"/home/admin/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"