{"type":"message","id":"0a9e2fe6","parentId":"a72f646e","timestamp":"2026-03-16T04:48:41.645Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems the skill is defined just by SKILL.md. The actual tools come from the openclaw-lark plugin. Let me check if I can call the feishu_wiki_space_node and feishu_wiki_space tools directly.\n\nActually, for this skill, I should create a script that will:\n1. Call feishu_wiki_space to get the space_id from the wiki_node\n2. Call feishu_wiki_space_node to list all nodes in the space\n3. Analyze and decide which directory to create the document in\n4. Call feishu_wiki_space_node to create the document\n5. Call feishu_mcp_create_doc to write content\n\nWait, there's already a feishu-create-doc skill. Let me see if I can just integrate with that.\n\nActually, the best approach would be to create a Python script that uses the OpenClaw tool system. Let me check how other skills implement their scripts.","thinkingSignature":"ca65a398ace5af0f27d48f786a9dc29752d30fff69dac6ca57d6efe0bfafb14d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xrn57ftkoa4o_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p ~/.openclaw/shared-skills/feishu-wiki-write/scripts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-cn","model":"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed","usage":{"input":37444,"output":238,"cacheRead":12787,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50469,"cost":{"input":0.022466399999999997,"output":0.0005712,"cacheRead":0.0007672199999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.023804819999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773636517570}}
